==Ancient Greek==

===Etymology===
From [[κῦρος]] ''(cyros,'' [[supremacy]]); supreme in authority, that is, (as noun) controller; by implication, Mr. (as a respectful title).

===Pronunciation===
* ''(traditional Greek)'' /ˈkirios/
* ''(Erasmian)'' /kýːriɔs/
* ''(reconstructed Homeric)'' /kúːriɔs/

===Adjective===
'''κύριος, -α, -ον''' ''(cyrios)''
# [[main]], [[major]], [[primary]], [[prime]], [[principal]]

===Noun===
'''κύριος, ὁ''' ''(cyrios,'' m.)
# [[God]], [[Lord]]
# [[master]], [[chief]], [[proprietor]], [[owner]], [[possessor]]
# [[mister]], [[sir]], [[gentleman]]

